        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I wonder that I can't create a SELF JOIN in FROM method of Zend_Db class.\r\n\r\nI use the following code:\r\n\r\n$qry_sel = $this->mdb_conn          ->SELECT()\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t->FROM(array(\"n\" => \"any_table\",\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t \"p\" => \"any_table\"),\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t array(\"n.col1\");\r\n\r\nAfter the code \r\n\r\n$this->mdb_conn->query($qry_sel);\r\n\r\nwas executed I only can see one alias table in from clause.\r\n\r\nI would be very useful to set more than one table in FROM method.\r\n\r\nbest regards\r\n"
        },
